														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-758014">
									

<p>The whole thing with new stars appearing doesn't sit well with me. It's just a little cliche and ridiculous at the same time. I mean, think about all the living matter that must unintentionally cross that bridge; insects, ect … that completely aside, it's weird to me that we could run a crate-full of squirrels across this thing and completely change the sky. Also it seems like a weird thing to notice.</p>
<p>The addendum is also cheesy I think … y'know, it occurs to me that the addendum would sound less cheesy if you left it, but took out the stars thing xD</p>
<p>I dunno, I thought you were going somewhere good with this and when I got to the stars bit I was a bit disappointed. I mean, if you take away the stars thing you'd have to add something else, because "bridge what makes you disappear" is ultimately a bland concept (even though it's very well written!).</p>

							</div>

								
